docs.abstract: The president at times stretched, ignored or made up facts, but in Japan and North and South Korea, he pursued an agenda of breathtaking ambition.
docs.snippet: The president at times stretched, ignored or made up facts, but in Japan and North and South Korea, he pursued an agenda of breathtaking ambition.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEOUL, South Korea — At one point during his eventful swing through Asia, President Trump took time out to slam Jimmy Carter. Responding to criticism from the former president, Mr. Trump hurled his usual insults. Then he unleashed this cutting barb: Mr. Carter, he said dismissively, was “the forgotten president.”

headline.main: Trump in Asia: ‘We’re the Hottest Show in Town’
headline.print_headline: Trump’s Trip to Asia: Diplomacy With an Exclamation Point

docs.abstract: Tensions between Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez and her “squad” have burst into the open, testing House Democratic unity.
docs.snippet: Tensions between Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez and her “squad” have burst into the open, testing House Democratic unity.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi said they have no following in Congress. Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez of New York shot back that she and three of her fellow liberal freshmen, darlings of the left known collectively as “the squad,” are wielding the real power in the party.

headline.main: Tensions Between Pelosi and Progressive Democrats of ‘the Squad’ Burst Into Flame
headline.print_headline: Discord With Young Progressives Tests Pelosi and Her Party’s Unity

docs.abstract: The decision blocks one of two lawsuits challenging the president over profits at his Washington hotel.
docs.snippet: The decision blocks one of two lawsuits challenging the president over profits at his Washington hotel.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In a legal victory for President Trump, a federal appeals court panel on Wednesday ordered the dismissal of a lawsuit claiming that he had violated the Constitution by collecting profits from government guests at his hotel in the nation’s capital.

headline.main: Federal Appeals Court Rules for Trump in Emoluments Case
headline.print_headline: Federal Appeals Court Blocks an Emoluments Lawsuit Against Trump

docs.abstract: The speaker, at an extraordinary, closed-door meeting of the House Democratic Caucus, tried to restore comity amid a dispute with four liberal freshmen and demanded an end to the public criticism.
docs.snippet: The speaker, at an extraordinary, closed-door meeting of the House Democratic Caucus, tried to restore comity amid a dispute with four liberal freshmen and demanded an end to the public criticism.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi, working to restore comity after her dispute with four liberal freshmen burst into the open, made an extraordinary closed-door plea for Democratic unity on Wednesday and sharply rebuked those who have made personal attacks against fellow Democrats.

headline.main: Pelosi Appeals for Democratic Unity While Dressing Down Dissenters
headline.print_headline: A Fiery Pelosi Calls for Democratic Unity

docs.abstract: The decision may have broader implications for how the First Amendment applies to officials’ accounts in the social-media era.
docs.snippet: The decision may have broader implications for how the First Amendment applies to officials’ accounts in the social-media era.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump has been violating the Constitution by blocking people from following his Twitter account because they criticized or mocked him, a federal appeals court ruled on Tuesday. The ruling could have broader implications for how the First Amendment applies to the social-media era.

headline.main: Trump Can’t Block Critics From His Twitter Account, Appeals Court Rules
headline.print_headline: Judges Decide Trump’s Tweets Are Open to All

docs.abstract: A former Air Force helicopter pilot who narrowly lost a bid for the House in November will challenge Senator John Cornyn, a Republican, in 2020.
docs.snippet: A former Air Force helicopter pilot who narrowly lost a bid for the House in November will challenge Senator John Cornyn, a Republican, in 2020.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A former Air Force helicopter pilot who nearly beat an incumbent Republican House member in the heart of Texas last year is launching another against-the-odds campaign — this time against Senator John Cornyn, a fixture in Texas Republican politics.

headline.main: M.J. Hegar, Veteran Armed With Viral Ads, Is Running for Senate in Texas

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The C.I.A. is quietly pushing Congress to significantly expand the scope of a law that makes it a crime to disclose the identities of undercover intelligence agents, raising alarms among advocates of press freedoms.

docs.abstract: Investigators for the inspector general recently interviewed Christopher Steele, the former British spy, as they try to determine whether the F.B.I. misstepped in the inquiry.
docs.snippet: Investigators for the inspector general recently interviewed Christopher Steele, the former British spy, as they try to determine whether the F.B.I. misstepped in the inquiry.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Inside a London office building in early June, three investigators for the Justice Department’s inspector general took a crucial step toward clearing the political fallout from the Russia investigation: They spent two days interviewing Christopher Steele, the former British spy whose now-infamous dossier of purported links between Trump associates and Russia ended up in the hands of the F.B.I. ahead of the 2016 election.

headline.main: Justice Dept. Watchdog Is Preparing to Deliver Verdict on the Russia Investigation
headline.print_headline: Watchdog Set to Size Up F.B.I.’s Russia Inquiry
